IF NOT EXISTS (SELECT * FROM sys.objects O JOIN sys.schemas S ON O.schema_id = S.schema_id WHERE O.NAME = '[Product]' AND O.TYPE = 'U' AND S.NAME = '[ext]')
CREATE TABLE [adventureworks_schema].[Product]
	(
	 [ProductID] int,
     [ModelName] nvarchar(4000),
	 [ProductName] nvarchar(4000),
     [Color] nvarchar(4000),
	 [ProductNumber] nvarchar(4000),
	 [ProductCategoryName] nvarchar(4000),
     [Size] nvarchar(4000),
     [ListPrice] float,
	 [StandardCost] float,
	 [Weight] float,
     [SellEndDateID] datetime2(0),
	 [SellStartDateID] datetime2(0),
	 [DiscontinuedDateID] nvarchar(4000),
     [ModifiedDateID] DATETIME2(0),
     [DescriptionCultureAr] nvarchar(4000),
     [DescriptionCultureEn] nvarchar(4000),
     [DescriptionCultureFr] nvarchar(4000),
     [DescriptionCultureHe] nvarchar(4000),
     [DescriptionCultureTh] nvarchar(4000),
     [DescriptionCultureZh-cht] nvarchar(4000),
	 [InsertedDate]nvarchar(4000),
     [HashKey] nvarchar(4000),
     [Status] nvarchar(4000)
	 
	)
WITH
	(
	DISTRIBUTION = ROUND_ROBIN,
	 HEAP
	)
GO
